        </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Why Digital Translations Fail</h3>
        <p>Arabic website localization fails when treated as simple translation. RTL layouts require more than mirroring—Arabic users expect native reading patterns, not awkward reversals. Direct keyword translation misses how Arabic speakers actually search, which often differs significantly from English patterns. Text expansion breaks carefully designed interfaces: Arabic is typically 20-30% longer than English, affecting button sizes, form layouts, and overall design. Our localization specialists understand these digital challenges from their web development and marketing backgrounds.</p>

